Preheat your oven to 200°C. Arrange the @sweet potato{200%g}(diced) on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle on a splash of @oil{}, season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and half the @Pasanda style seasoning{1/2%portion}. Use your hands to rub the flavours over the sweet potato. Lay out in one even layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Bring the @water{300%ml} to the boil in a large #saucepan{} over high heat. When boiling, stir in and dissolve the @vegetable stock powder{1/2%portion}. Stir in the @quinoa{120%g} and remaining @Pasanda style seasoning{1/2%portion} and bring back to the boil. Lower the heat and simmer until the quinoa has doubled in size and the seed has visibly split, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain into a #sieve{} and return to the pan off the heat. Cover with a #lid{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}, remove the core and seeds then slice thinly. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can} in the sieve. Remove the @pistachios{25%g} from their shells, discard the shells and roughly chop the nuts. Halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the onion and pepper and stir-fry until softened, ~{5%minutes}. After 5 mins, add the black beans and warm through. Stir in and wilt the @baby spinach{62.5%g} a handful at a time, this will take another ~{2-3%minutes}.

When the spinach is wilted, stir in the @mango chutney{80%g} and remove from the heat. Carefully mix in the sweet potato. Season to taste with salt, pepper and a squeeze of lemon juice. Get ready to serve.

Fluff the quinoa up with a #fork{} and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, a squeeze of lemon juice and half the coriander. Share the quinoa between your bowls. Top with the veggies and finish with small dollops of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and a sprinkling of pistachios and the remaining coriander. Enjoy!